msgid "About Daily Logos"
msgstr ""

#: lib/daily_logos_web/controllers/page_html/about.html.heex:31
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Daily Logos pairs every day of the year with a carefully chosen quote from the Stoic tradition. Open the app on any given day and you'll find a single passage worth sitting with. Nothing more, nothing less."
msgstr ""

#: lib/daily_logos_web/controllers/page_html/about.html.heex:73
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "How to get the most out of it"
msgstr ""

#: lib/daily_logos_web/controllers/page_html/about.html.heex:13
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Inspired by The Daily Stoic by Ryan Holiday and Stephen Hanselman. Not affiliated with or endorsed by the authors or their publisher."
msgstr ""

#: lib/daily_logos_web/controllers/page_html/about.html.heex:76
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Read the quote slowly. Then read it again. If something in it catches your attention, hold onto it for the day and notice whether it changes how you handle a situation. That's it. There is no streak to maintain, no score to keep."
msgstr ""

#: lib/daily_logos_web/controllers/page_html/feedback.html.heex:10
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Share your thoughts."
msgstr ""

#: lib/daily_logos_web/controllers/page_html/about.html.heex:61
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Stoicism is practical. It does not ask you to withdraw from the world or adopt a particular lifestyle. It asks you to pay attention to what you can control, accept what you cannot, and act well in the space between. That advice has held up for roughly two thousand years, which suggests it might be onto something."
msgstr ""

#: lib/daily_logos_web/components/layouts/app_header.ex:45
#: lib/daily_logos_web/components/layouts/main_menu.ex:67
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "Support"
msgstr ""

#: lib/daily_logos_web/controllers/page_html/about.html.heex:36
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The 365 quotes are organized into monthly themes that follow a loose arc across the year, from clarity and focus in the early months to resilience and gratitude toward the end. The rhythm is intentional: returning day after day is the whole point."
msgstr ""

#: lib/daily_logos_web/controllers/page_html/about.html.heex:49
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The collection draws from the three writers who define the Stoic canon: Marcus Aurelius, who ruled an empire and still found time to remind himself that anger is a choice; Epictetus, the freed slave who taught that freedom is a state of mind; and Seneca, whose letters to a friend remain some of the most honest writing about how to actually live well. Together, they cover almost every situation a modern life can throw at you."
msgstr ""

#: lib/daily_logos_web/controllers/page_html/about.html.heex:46
#, elixir-autogen, elixir-format
msgid "The voices behind the quotes"
